{"body": "<p>For a batch(.bat) type install of this, you would need to do something like the following:</p>\n\n<pre><code>httpd.exe -k install -n \"MyServiceName\"\nsc config \"MyServiceName\"  start=demand\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>References,</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://windowsitpro.com/systems-management/how-can-i-configure-services-start-type-command-line\" rel=\"nofollow\">sc application to configure the service</a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.makeuseof.com/tag/write-simple-batch-bat-file/\" rel=\"nofollow\">saving to a batch file</a></p>\n", "tags": ["windows", "winforms", "service"], "creation_date": 1469206984, "score": 0, "last_activity_date": 1469206984, "answer_id": 38531863, "is_accepted": true, "owner": {"user_id": 690141, "reputation": 1764, "user_type": "registered", "display_name": "Jimmy Smith", "link": "http://stackoverflow.com/users/690141/jimmy-smith", "profile_image": "https://i.stack.imgur.com/ToONn.jpg?s=128&g=1"}, "title": "Change Apache Service Startup type to Manual", "question_id": 38528922}